Gitiles - A simple JGit repository browser
==========================================

Gitiles is a simple repository browser for Git repositories, built on JGit. Its
guiding principle is simplicity: it has no formal access controls, no write
access, no fancy Javascript, etc.

BUILDING

Gitiles requires Maven (http://maven.apache.org/) to build.

sudo apt-get install maven
cd gitiles
mvn compile


TESTING

cd gitiles
mvn package
./tools/run_dev.sh
open http://localhost:8080/ to view your local copy of gitiles.

===================================================
Changed by Keven Liu(airk908@gmail.com)@2013.07.10.
Usage:

1.Write your own gitiles.config
follow gitiles.config.sample(Thanks to http://hron.me/blog/2013/01/gitiles-install-howto/).

2.Start your own Git service

$:./tools/run_dev.sh start

3.Stop the Git service

$:./tools/run_dev.sh stop
